Serenity: Art in Meditation Exhibit at the Thomas Center Galleries
28
Aug
2025
Friday, June 27 - Saturday, Aug. 30
The exhibition explores how the creation of art is used to promote mind, body and spirit in various forms of meditation.
Historic Thomas Center Galleries, 302 NW Sixth Ave.,  32601

Free Fridays Concert Series
29
Aug
2025
The region’s longest-running and largest free outdoor concert series features local and regional musical talent at the Bo Diddley Plaza.  Our concerts under the stars showcase diverse musical acts sure to delight music lovers with classic rock, reggae, R & B, soul, ska, funk, blues and more.
Bo Diddley Plaza, 111 E. University Ave.,  32601

Mindful Movement
30
Aug
2025
Join us for a serene and empowering mindful movement session, combining the joyful expression of Nia with the meditative flow of SloMo. Offered in accompaniment to the Serenity art exhibition at the Thomas Center, this all-levels session includes grounding breathwork, slow-flow movement and closing seated meditation. No experience necessary.
The Historic Thomas Center, 302 NW Sixth Ave.,  32601
